  "body": "- [X] I've asked for help in the [Truffle Gitter](http://gitter.im/Consensys/truffle) before filing this issue.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\nWithout active internet connection, truffle fails to compile contracts with the following error:\r\n`Error: Failed to complete request to: https://solc-bin.ethereum.org/bin/list.json. Are you connected to the internet?`\r\nThis is acceptable when using solcjs and truffle does not have required version cached but I am using native solc so it shouldn't have to contact the internet.\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\nDisconnect your internet and use `truffle compile`\r\nOR\r\nSwitch your ISP to comcast and try truffle compile.\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\nIt should just compile the contracts using native solc without needing to fetch any data from the internet.\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n`Error: Failed to complete request to: https://solc-bin.ethereum.org/bin/list.json. Are you connected to the internet?`\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n* Operating System: Ubuntu bionic\r\n* Ethereum client: Ganache\r\n* Truffle v5.0.0 (core: 5.0.0)\r\n* Solidity - native (solc-js)\r\n* Node v8.12.0\r\n\r\nps. Removing the need of contacting the internet should also be a possible optimization. Now that native solc is faster than ferrari, fetching data from interent takes a considerable percent of compile time.\r\n",
